Jun 8 2007 	We Liked This Hotel!	We stayed at the Marriott Courtyard Fisherman’s Warf for four nights beginning May 30th, 2007. We found the hotel to be a clean, well kept and good value. The staff was friendly and helpful. The hotel is located on Beach Street on the west end Fisherman’s Warf within easy walking distance to the Cable Car turntable near Ghirardelli Square and to the attractions in the Fisherman’s Warf area. Self parking is available in the parking garage next door and hotel guests have in-and-out privileges. The room was spacious and clean with white bed linens and comforter. The all too common polyester bedspread was replaced with a simple runner at the foot of the bed designed to keep the white comforter clean if luggage is placed on the foot of the bed. The bed was comfortable and ample pillows were supplied (five per bed). The bathroom was clean and had a full-size tub and shower combination with the sink cabinet running the full length on the opposite wall. The air conditioner / heater was a self-contained unit and was quiet when the compressor cycled on and off. A nice feature of the unit was the ability to have the fan run continuously regardless of the compressor operation. This allowed for a soft white noise that I find helpful for a good sleep. Another plus was the free high speed internet service. Breakfast is available in the hotel. The full Courtyard Buffet is priced at $12.95 and the Continental Buffet priced at $8.95. A La Carte breakfasts are available beginning at $8.95. We are not big breakfast eaters, and we opted for less expensive fare elsewhere. The hotel is equipped with two guest washers and driers on the second floor. The cost to run a load of wash is $1.50 and $1.00 to dry. Complementary detergent and fabric softener is available at the front desk. Overall, we really liked the hotel. A note about the weather. If you are coming expecting the warm, sunny California experience that’s not San Francisco – which is ok, just be prepared. While we were here the temperatures were between the mid 50’s and the lower 60’s, with a good breeze off the water. The combination of temperature, wind, and overcast skies can lead to a chilly experience if you are from a warmer climate. Many folks are apparently caught off guard by this since you see crowds of people all wearing new San Francisco jackets and sweatshirts.	
